    "narrative": "For the Austin Waves on this April 29th, the trio of **Jackson Merrill** (74.85), **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.84), and **Kyle Tucker** (73.39) headline our optimal lineup. **Jackson Merrill** benefits significantly from leading off against Taillon, where his aggressive plate approach aligns with a favorable platoon split (+13%). Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** provides the highest floor of the day, bolstered by an elite 31-PA BvP historical edge (+8%) against Bello and a strong xwOBA profile. **Josh Lowe** (71.68) also demands attention; while his base projection is moderate, he is our prime candidate for stolen base production today, specifically because Fedde\u2019s slow delivery offers a 93% success rate for swipes, pushing **Josh Lowe** into the \"Strong\" start tier.\n\nThe optimizer faced its toughest decision regarding the utility spot, ultimately favoring **Marcell Ozuna** (60.22) over **Miguel Vargas** (58.95). While **Miguel Vargas** offers solid order value hitting second, the combination of wind blowing out and a slightly superior SP skill adjustment for **Marcell Ozuna** against Pallante gave the veteran the narrow edge. Conversely, we must exercise caution with **Heliot Ramos** (46.99); although he leads off against a lefty, the 40% rain risk creates significant volatility. Furthermore, **Jacob Wilson** (70.34) remains a high-upside play assuming he slots into the leadoff position against Wacha, but he is sensitive to the final lineup posting. \n\nWe are officially pivoting away from **Gunnar Henderson** today due to a confirmed rainout, ensuring we don't burn a game cap on a DNP. While we have depth waiting on the bench\u2014specifically **Brady House**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Coby Mayo**, **Nolan Schanuel**, and **Dominic Smith**\u2014the efficiency gap between our starters and these reserves remains substantial enough that no late-swap actions are currently required to optimize our 5x5 output. **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks** provide necessary coverage behind the plate, though they face stiff tests against elite arms Skubal and Glasnow, respectively.",
